President Barack Obama and First Lady Michelle Obama met with Malala Yousafzai in the Oval Office to express gratitude for her inspiring work advocating for girls' education in Pakistan. The United States stands with Pakistan and others around the world in celebrating Malala's courage and determination in promoting the right of all girls to attend school and pursue their dreams. The First Lady believes that investing in girls' education benefits not only the girls themselves but also their families, communities, and countries. The President, in his proclamation marking the International Day of the Girl, emphasized the importance of giving girls the opportunity to choose their own destinies and change the world. The White House commends Malala for her efforts in helping to fulfill these dreams.